This paper discusses continual learning for autonomous agents and robots, which involves the development of artificial intelligence and machine learning models that can learn from continuous streams of information without forgetting previously learned representations. The paper focuses on biological learning factors and their computational counterparts for modeling the progressive acquisition of increasingly complex knowledge and skills in a continual fashion. Given this focus, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
